    <briefdescription>
<para>SPI scatter-gather buffer array structure. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>A <ref refid="structspi__buf__set" kindref="compound">spi_buf_set</ref> is a flexible description of a whole single SPI bus transfer.</para>
<para>Since the set is an array of pointers to buffers, it means that pieces of a spi transfer definition can be re-used across different transfers, without having to redefine or allocate new memory for them each time. This accomplishes what is called &quot;scatter-gather&quot; buffer management at the driver level with user-provided buffers. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
